metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #511
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Different Intersections - Iteration 4 #290
metadata.description:
This is the culmination of a series of iterations

____ - Iteration 1
____ - Iteration 2
____ - Iteration 3

The iterations were released under the pseudonym Extracurricular Activities.

The algorithmic theme of the iterations was extensive usage of boolean operations (intersection and difference) on polygons to derive interesting composite shapes.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Bento Boxes #126
metadata.description:
Everybody needs a bento box in the cryptowinter.
The project calls for an adopted nostalgia of little kids that has been handed bento box by their parents before school— a little moment of protected comfort before heading out for an adventure.

• • •

The first collaboration project of MEK.txt and IceRain in FXHash. A work based on MEK.txt’s “The Bento Boxes” and IceRain’s excellent codes, Bento Boxes aims to be a fun visual and code exploration project on the generative art corridor. Pure code, no libraries.

Bento Boxes deconstructed the visual system on MEK.txt's artwork, titled almost similarly, “The Bento Boxes”. Rebuilt it from scratch with codes, adding variants of colours and shapes— without losing the strong characteristics of the base artwork.

metadata.name: Nothing Remains #71
metadata.description:
The only time I ever received corporal punishment – something that was still legal in schools during the 1970s – was in Double Maths with Mrs Robinson. The log book spread out before me seemed less appealing than talking with my friends at the back of the classroom, and so it was I found myself, palm outstretched, feeling the whack of Mrs. Robinson's ruler, ten times over. "Math sucks." Or so I thought.

Back then I knew nothing of the beauty that I would later see in Mathematics – something which became apparent as I taught myself to code, especially using Processing.

This work – based on code I've been playing around with since 2009 – is my small homage to that beauty. Originally based on Ulam spirals, I've then played around with that starting formula to create an infinite numbers of patterns using square roots, cosines and modulus. If only they had shown me these possibilities when I was younger I may have avoided the dreaded ruler of Mrs. Robinson.

metadata.name: Out—Land #1
metadata.description:
Nowhere but here, before—a prequel, of sorts,
with nothing yet built to fall;
a jagged canvas,
unowned, unknown…
brutal even if naive

——

A : Animate rendering
S : Save at 2000x2500 pixels
1 -> 5 : Save 3000x3750 -> 7000x8750
(incrementing width 1000 pixels with each step)

metadata.name: Fever Dream Fairy Fantasy Forest #234
metadata.description:
A strange place where you can't tell the trees from the sky, the clouds from the shrubs, or where your body ends and the ground begins.

Press [s] in live view to capture a 2048x2048 screenshot



XALTED 2022

metadata.name: contrapuntos #464
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: City Pop - AI Study II #156
metadata.description:
City Pop takes you to a lively and geometric city created by digital architects. The use of shapes, colors, and lines causes visionary hallucinations leading the viewer to imaginary places filled with endless possibilities.

This project is a generative art experiment using a Text2Code workflow. The JavaScript code for this project was written entirely by AI using GPT-3. None of the code was altered or created by a human aside from changing Math.random() with fxrand().

Text2Code study #2 /// Project CoDexter by @BrainArtLabs

metadata.name: Neo Supremus #81
metadata.description:
A generative ode to Kasimir Sewerinowitsch Malewitsch's suprematist compositions.

In live view, press 'S' to save a high rez version of the sketch.

metadata.name: Sap song. Part II #235
metadata.description:
This artwork corresponds to the 2nd part of the ‘Sap song’ series. It seeks to expand the concept from new visual and sound variants.

Audiovisual generative artwork that continues with the proposal of excessive flows of organic forms. In time, frenetic arpeggios and populations of colorful plants with spiral flowers are emerging, all organized in their own way. And the sap again sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

The work has 3 moments:
I. “Enredo coral”
II. “Recitativo libre”
III. “Coda hacia la raíz”

Original samplers of cello pizzicatos, marimba, music box, piano, and multiphonics of clarinet and flute.

[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen

attributes.value: cello, marimba, music box and flute

metadata.name: AI Brain Scheme #376
metadata.description:
Simple project using trigonometry, recursive function 
and simple geometry shapes to create an imaginary AI Brain Scheme

You can download the large image to see the small detail.

---
Features : 
AI Grid Configurator : True/False
AI Extra Brain Chips : True/False
Ai Binary Dreams Code : True/False
Photonic Wire : True/False

AI Level : 9 Levels (Very Small AI-Small AI-Medium AI-Medium x2 AI-Large AI-Large x2 AI-Impossible AI-Insane AI-Quantum Level AI)
"Quantum Level AI" = super rare

Color Schemes : red,blue,green
---
Unlimited colors palette
---
Press [p] to save captured image to png (3300pxx4500px)
---
Created using vanilla javascript
